         <abstract>
            <p>The problem considered in this paper is that of finding longest chains of the type: r&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;, r&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;, r&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;/sub&gt;, ⋯, r&lt;sub&gt;m&lt;/sub&gt;, for which the m(m + 1)/2 sums r&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt; + r&lt;sub&gt;i+1&lt;/sub&gt; + r&lt;sub&gt;i+2&lt;/sub&gt; + ⋯ + r&lt;sub&gt;j&lt;/sub&gt;, 1 ≤ i ≤ j ≤ m, will be distinct quadratic residues of a given prime p.</p>
          </abstract>
